WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.660
Bentornato!

00:00:01.660 --> 00:00:04.301
L'ultima volta hai visto

00:00:04.301 --> 00:00:06.282
i comandi fork.

00:00:06.282 --> 00:00:08.923
Ora vediamo cosa significano

00:00:08.923 --> 00:00:09.583
davvero:

00:00:09.583 --> 00:00:11.564
un'app database live,

00:00:11.564 --> 00:00:14.205
copiata in pochi secondi,

00:00:14.205 --> 00:00:15.526
modificata liberamente,

00:00:15.526 --> 00:00:18.167
mentre l'originale non se

00:00:18.167 --> 00:00:20.148
ne accorge minimamente.

00:00:20.933 --> 00:00:22.725
Ecco la situazione:

00:00:22.725 --> 00:00:25.713
un PostgreSQL reale con un'interfaccia

00:00:25.713 --> 00:00:26.907
pgAdmin sopra,

00:00:26.907 --> 00:00:28.700
attivo sul server.

00:00:28.700 --> 00:00:31.687
Un fork è un gemello

00:00:31.687 --> 00:00:34.674
copy-on-write istantaneo di tutto questo.

00:00:34.674 --> 00:00:37.064
Stessi dati alla nascita,

00:00:37.064 --> 00:00:39.454
vite completamente separate dopo.

00:00:42.716 --> 00:00:44.350
Meet the app:

00:00:44.350 --> 00:00:44.894
demo-pgadmin,

00:00:44.894 --> 00:00:47.617
a PostgreSQL with a pgAdmin

00:00:47.617 --> 00:00:48.162
interface,

00:00:48.162 --> 00:00:49.795
mounted and running.

00:00:52.795 --> 00:00:54.265
Un repo live.

00:00:54.265 --> 00:00:54.754
Cloniamolo.

00:00:55.266 --> 00:00:56.485
Questo è l'originale,

00:00:56.485 --> 00:00:57.297
nel browser.

00:00:57.297 --> 00:00:58.922
pgAdmin chiede un login,

00:00:58.922 --> 00:01:01.359
perché è la copia di produzione,

00:01:01.359 --> 00:01:03.390
e la produzione rimane protetta.

00:01:28.933 --> 00:01:29.741
Fork it.

00:01:29.741 --> 00:01:32.572
The copy-on-write clone takes seconds regardless of

00:01:32.572 --> 00:01:32.976
size;

00:01:32.976 --> 00:01:35.807
detach returns as soon as the containers

00:01:35.807 --> 00:01:36.211
start,

00:01:36.211 --> 00:01:39.042
while health checks continue in the background.

00:01:39.301 --> 00:01:40.079
Fork avviato.

00:01:40.079 --> 00:01:42.413
I dati non sono stati copiati,

00:01:42.413 --> 00:01:43.581
sono stati condivisi,

00:01:43.581 --> 00:01:46.304
finché uno dei due lati non li

00:01:46.304 --> 00:01:46.693
modifica.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:52.485
E qui c'è il pgAdmin del

00:01:52.485 --> 00:01:52.908
fork.

00:01:52.908 --> 00:01:54.598
Nessun login questa volta:

00:01:54.598 --> 00:01:57.133
i fork sono sandbox usa e

00:01:57.133 --> 00:01:57.556
getta,

00:01:57.556 --> 00:02:00.091
quindi il cancello si fa da

00:02:00.091 --> 00:02:00.514
parte.

00:02:00.514 --> 00:02:01.359
Stesse tabelle,

00:02:01.359 --> 00:02:02.204
stesse righe,

00:02:02.204 --> 00:02:04.317
ma il suo universo separato.

00:02:41.816 --> 00:02:43.024
Two repositories now:

00:02:43.024 --> 00:02:45.037
the original and the experiment,

00:02:45.037 --> 00:02:47.050
each with its own containers,

00:02:47.050 --> 00:02:47.453
network,

00:02:47.453 --> 00:02:48.660
and disk view.

00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:52.737
Stessa macchina,

00:02:52.737 --> 00:02:54.351
due mondi isolati.

00:02:57.652 --> 00:02:58.573
Done experimenting?

00:02:58.573 --> 00:02:59.955
Delete the fork.

00:02:59.955 --> 00:03:01.337
Seconds to create,

00:03:01.337 --> 00:03:04.100
seconds to throw away — the

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:06.403
original never knew it existed.

00:03:09.403 --> 00:03:09.855
Eliminato.

00:03:09.855 --> 00:03:12.567
L'originale ha continuato a rispondere per

00:03:12.567 --> 00:03:13.923
tutto il tempo.

00:03:14.723 --> 00:03:16.930
Quindi fai fork liberamente,

00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:19.689
la produzione non può essere

00:03:19.689 --> 00:03:20.240
danneggiata.

00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:22.447
Prossimamente esaminiamo i secrets,

00:03:22.447 --> 00:03:25.206
l'unica cosa che i tuoi

00:03:25.206 --> 00:03:27.413
fork deliberatamente non ereditano.

00:03:27.413 --> 00:03:28.516
A presto!
